``At Littleton, America got a glimpse of the last stop on that train to hell America boarded decades ago when we declared that God is dead and that each of us is his or her own god who can make up the rules as we go along.''
Calling the return to the classroom ``a very important next step  in the process of healing,'' Monseu said the first thing Columbine students will do when they arrive at Chatfield High School is attend an assembly to reunite them with their teachers.
``And we've got to take advantage of our time with our familyand friends,'' Aimee Jensen, 18, added quietly.
